text: Austin D Verner (born 1943), is a male former swimmer who competed for England. ==Swimming career== He represented England in the 440 yards freestyle event, at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Perth, Western Australia. He swam for the Urmston Swimming Club. ==References== Category:1943 births Category:English male swimmers Category:Swimmers at the 1962 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Living people Category:Male freestyle swimmers
